  "texts": [
    "A critic might object, it is simply inappropriate to think of programs like ChatGPT as hard bullshitters, because (i) they are not agents, or relatedly, (ii) they do not and cannot intend anything whatsoever.",
    "We think this is too fast.",
    "First, whether or not ChatGPT has agency, its creators and users do.",
    "And what they produce with it, we will argue, is bullshit.",
    "Second, we will argue that, regardless of whether it has agency, it does have a function; this function gives it characteristic goals, and possibly even intentions, which align with our definition of hard bullshit."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}